      { question: "A patient on metformin 2000 mg daily has an eGFR that has declined to 38 mL/min. What is the appropriate metformin adjustment?", options: ["Continue current dose — metformin is safe at all GFR levels", "Reduce to maximum 1000 mg daily", "Discontinue metformin immediately", "Switch to insulin"], correctIndex: 1, rationale: "At eGFR 30-45 mL/min, metformin should be dose-reduced to a maximum of 1000 mg daily. It should be discontinued at eGFR <30 mL/min. Current guidelines allow continued use with dose adjustment at this GFR range, balancing glycemic benefit with the small increased risk of lactic acidosis.", isFree: true }
